244
00:25:20,009 --> 00:25:23,719
To do anything for them and for the others, I had to negotiate.

245
00:25:25,013 --> 00:25:29,563
<i>Dallaire carried on through the next gate to confront the extremist leadership.</i>

246
00:25:30,949 --> 00:25:38,099
<i>But he decided not to mention his troops, who he knew were being beaten 200 yards away.</i>

247
00:25:43,048 --> 00:25:48,648
Gen. ROMEO DALLAIRE: 
What I said was, "Get a grip of your units. I'm staying."

248
00:25:55,641 --> 00:26:06,341
The informant, Jean-Pierre, had told us that they were trying to set up to wipe out a dozen or so or 10 Belgians in order to break the back of our mission

249
00:26:06,410 --> 00:26:16,000
because if the Belgians pulled out, I had no real substantive capability to sustain myself, and that the international community would pull us all out.

250
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,292
These guys knew about Mogadishu also.

251
00:26:19,616 --> 00:26:26,006
And so what I was making clear to them was, is that I'm staying.

252
00:26:28,087 --> 00:26:36,437
<i>Dallaire later demanded to know what had happened to the Belgians, but he took no military action to rescue his troops.</i>

253
00:26:39,558 --> 00:26:49,008
Gen. ROMEO DALLAIRE: 
Finally, a phone call, after insistence, came in 
and said that they are all at the hospital,

254
00:26:51,456 --> 00:26:53,136
at the morgue.

255
00:26:53,955 --> 00:26:55,155
And so I said, "Right. Let's go."

256
00:26:57,024 --> 00:26:59,776
Morgue was a little shack,

257
00:26:59,777 --> 00:27:03,917
and a bit of an L-shaped small shack.

258
00:27:04,704 --> 00:27:08,004
And it was a 24-watt bulb, at best.

259
00:27:10,098 --> 00:27:17,008
And there in the corner of the L-shape was this pile of potato bags,

