315
00:34:18,606 --> 00:34:21,906
<i>Dozens of journalists had arrived with the new troops.</i>

316
00:34:22,082 --> 00:34:27,899
<i>They traveled with Belgian soldiers to Kigali's psychiatric hospital, where the Western staff was trapped.</i>

317
00:34:32,654 --> 00:34:37,104
<i>On the way in, they drove past the Interahamwe waiting outside.</i>

318
00:34:42,045 --> 00:34:46,695
<i>Tutsis emerged from the hospital building, where they'd been hiding for three days.</i>

319
00:34:48,896 --> 00:34:53,996
<i>They said they were surrounded by the militias, that some of them had already been killed.</i>

320
00:35:01,217 --> 00:35:06,967
<i>When it was clear the soldiers weren't going to help, the refugees appealed to the journalists.</i>

321
00:35:20,076 --> 00:35:28,519
KATELIJNE HERMANS, Belgian Television: 
There was a whole group of people, but in the whole group, one woman started to speak and started to explain why they were afraid and what was happening to them.

322
00:35:28,544 --> 00:35:33,482
And she started begging us to take her and the others with us.

323
00:35:35,873 --> 00:35:42,223
She was speaking to me, a woman to a woman, saying, "I'm afraid. Please help me!"

324
00:35:43,479 --> 00:35:47,129
And we were just listening to her, and we couldn't do anything.

325
00:35:48,931 --> 00:35:53,131
At that moment, we thought we couldn't do anything, just listen and say "Yes."

326
00:36:01,053 --> 00:36:02,973
So we left.

327
00:36:03,675 --> 00:36:10,175
For the white people, it's over, but we knew the hundreds that stayed.

328
00:36:11,220 --> 00:36:16,720
And we heard the shooting at the moment we left. 
So it was clear for me that hell starts for them.

329
00:36:22,083 --> 00:36:29,433
<i>All Western troops and U.N. peacekeepers were under orders not to evacuate ordinary Rwandans.</i>

330
00:36:30,897 --> 00:36:38,207
Maj. BRENT BEARDSLEY: 
